HEADWORD: Panpresbyterian
<hw>Pan`pres`by*te"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pan-</ets> + <ets>Presbyterian</ets>.]</ety> <def>Belonging
to, or representative of, those who hold Presbyterian views in all parts
of the world; <as>as, a <ex>Panpresbyterian</ex> council</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
